@startuml state-dir-trail-memory
'' PlantUML state diagram: Alt+Up / Alt+Down walk the directory hierarchy while a persisted dir→child
'' trail makes the walk reversible — Alt+Up then Alt+Down returns to the most-recently-opened full path.
'' (PlantUML over Mermaid: explicit state machine with guard-style transition notes.)
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title Alt+Up / Alt+Down over the persisted directory→child trail

state "Viewing  /a/b/c.md\n(a file)" as FILE
state "Browsing  /a/b\nhighlight = c.md" as DIRB
state "Browsing  /a\nhighlight = b" as DIRA

[*] --> FILE : open /a/b/c.md\nrecord-recent writes\n/→a, /a→b, /a/b→c.md

FILE --> DIRB : **Alt+Up**  (:nav/parent → /a/b)
DIRB --> DIRA : **Alt+Up**  (:nav/parent → /a)
DIRA --> DIRB : **Alt+Down**  (:nav/open-target opens b → /a/b,\nhighlight = trail[/a/b] = c.md)
DIRB --> FILE : **Alt+Down**  (opens c.md)

note right of DIRB
  highlight = nav/effective-selected:
   • explicit dir-selected (if a current child)
   • else trail[dir]
   • else the first listed entry
end note

note bottom
  The trail lives in recent.edn ([:ui :recent :trail]) and persists across
  sessions, so revisiting /a/b in a later run still highlights c.md. Each
  Alt+Up / Alt+Down also pushes the per-tab history (Alt+Left undoes it).
end note
@enduml
